Rolling blackouts and cable theft are only making matters worse for Chris Hani Baragwanath hospital. The constant tripping of electricity at the hospital is now causing internal system issues which saw all 16 of its generators kicking in over the weekend. Power has since been restored, but City Power has red-flagged the hospital as a concern. eNCA’s Heidi Giokos reports. #DStv403 JOHANNESBURG - One of the biggest hospitals in South Africa -- Chris Hani Baragwanath -- seems to be having electricity problems. The hospital had to rely on all its generators over the weekend before power was restored on Monday. The hospital says the constant interruption of electricity supply is playing havoc with the hospital's internal power management systems. City Power managed to restore power to the hospital by Monday, enabling the hospital to resolve its system issues. While services weren’t interrupted, there is concern at the regularity of power cuts. * eNCA’s Heidi Giokos reports.